Boko Haram insurgents are currently burning houses in Mifa, a village in Chibok local government area of Borno state. According to the TheCable, the insurgents arrived the village in large numbers around 8pm, and immediately began to set houses ablaze. “They are burning houses as I speak to you, many of them arrived with motorcycles and started attacking the village,” a source told The Cable “Many houses have been burnt.” Details subsequently…